explanation: The algorithm iteratively compares the first character of the input string `s` with the last character of the output string `p`. It appends the smaller character to `p` and removes the last character of `p` if the first character of `s` is lexicographically greater. This process continues until both strings are empty, resulting in the lexicographically smallest possible output string.

